<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1149,1519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Notes.— 
<bibRefCitation author="Boata, A." box="[302,453,1222,1248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="327 - 348" refId="ref33670" refString="Boata, A. (1988) Microevolution in Solatopupa landsnails (Pulmonata Chondrinidae): genetic diversity and founder effects. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 34, 327 - 348." type="journal article" year="1988">Boata (1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Boata, A." box="[469,528,1222,1248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="345 - 354" refId="ref33705" refString="Boata, A. (1991) Allozyme versus discrete morphologic characters in the phylogenetic analysis of the land snail Solatopupa (Pulmonata, Chondrinidae). Bollettino di Zoologia, 58, 345 - 354." type="journal article" year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
) has reconstructed a phylogeny for the genus using karyological data, and molecular (allozymes) and morphological characters. Her work revealed the existence of a cryptic species, for which the name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Issel, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Issel" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[351,625,1300,1326]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Solatopupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="juliana">
<emphasis box="[351,466,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. juliana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Issel, A." box="[485,617,1300,1326]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref35403" refString="Issel, A. (1866) Dei molluschi raccolti nella provincia di Pisa. Memorie della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali e del Museo Civico de Storia Naturale di Milano, 2, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1866">Issel, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was available. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ketmaier, V. &amp; Giusti, F. &amp; Caccone, A." box="[813,1080,1300,1326]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="439 - 451" refId="ref35518" refString="Ketmaier, V., Giusti, F. &amp; Caccone, A. (2006) Molecular phylogeny and historical biogeography of the land snail genus Solatopupa (Pulmonata) in the peri-Tyrrhenian area. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 39, 439 - 451." type="journal article" year="2006">Ketmaier et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
provided a phylogeny reconstruction for the genus on the basis of DNA sequencing data. In that reconstruction 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Caziot" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1139,1278,1339,1364]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Solatopupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cianensis">
<emphasis box="[1139,1278,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. cianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
takes a basal position among the 
<taxonomicName box="[383,611,1377,1403]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Solatopupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[383,516,1377,1402]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Solatopupa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, which is not congruent with the findings of 
<bibRefCitation author="Boata, A." box="[1135,1282,1377,1403]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="327 - 348" refId="ref33670" refString="Boata, A. (1988) Microevolution in Solatopupa landsnails (Pulmonata Chondrinidae): genetic diversity and founder effects. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 34, 327 - 348." type="journal article" year="1988">Boata (1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Boata, A." box="[1294,1357,1377,1403]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="345 - 354" refId="ref33705" refString="Boata, A. (1991) Allozyme versus discrete morphologic characters in the phylogenetic analysis of the land snail Solatopupa (Pulmonata, Chondrinidae). Bollettino di Zoologia, 58, 345 - 354." type="journal article" year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
